name: Air Fryer Chicken Fajita Taquitos
author: thedailygourmet
summary: This recipe takes some time to prepare, but the results are SO worth it!
ingredients: 2 (4 ounce) boneless, skinless chicken breasts, cut into strips
1 (14 ounce) package fire-roasted peppers and onion blend (such as Trader Joe's®), thawed
directions: Place chicken strips in a sealable container and add marinade
Seal and allow to marinate for 2 hours
Heat a skillet over medium-high heat and cook chicken strips until browned, 6 to 7 minutes
Add thawed peppers and onions and cook for 2 to 3 minutes more
Transfer chicken strips to a cutting board and chop into smaller pieces
Add chopped chicken back to the peppers and onions; stir to combine
Preheat an heat air fryer to 370 degrees F (187 degrees C) for 5 minutes
Place tortillas in a tortilla bag
Microwave 5 tortillas at a time for 30 seconds
Spray each side of warmed tortillas with about 1/2 teaspoon oil and lay on a cutting board
Place 1 to 2 tablespoons chicken filling on top and sprinkle with 1 tablespoon cheese blend
Place taquitos seam-side down in the air fryer basket and air fry for 5 minutes
Increase air fryer temperature to  400 degrees F (200 degrees C) and air fry for 5 minutes more
